# Data Handling Patterns

All application data fetching and mutations must go through helper functions in `src/db/queries`.

- Put reusable database read and write helpers in `src/db/queries`.
- Server components should call query helpers for database reads instead of importing `db` directly.
- Server actions should validate inputs, then call query helpers for inserts, updates, and deletes.
- Query helpers must use Drizzle and import tables and columns from [src/db/schema.ts](mdc:src/db/schema.ts).
- Do not duplicate database query logic in route handlers, components, or server actions when it belongs in `src/db/queries`.
